# easycopy

easycopy converts any GitHub repository into one clean static HTML document, optimized for quick reading by humans and high-signal context ingestion by LLMs.

## Problem

Large repositories are hard to scan quickly. Important details are fragmented across folders, READMEs, and code files. This slows down onboarding, review, and AI-assisted development.

## Solution

- Generates a single consolidated HTML view of a repo
- Makes structure and key files easier to parse in one pass
- Helps teams share "repo snapshots" without requiring IDE setup
- Includes MCP support so AI tools can reason over bigger codebases with lower friction

## Why it matters

easycopy reduces the time between "I found a repo" and "I understand this repo." It's built for engineers, reviewers, and AI workflows that need clarity fast.
